org.magnos.asset.source
Class ClasspathSource

java.lang.Object
  org.magnos.asset.base.BaseAssetSource
      org.magnos.asset.source.ClasspathSource
All Implemented Interfaces:
AssetSource
public class ClasspathSource
extends BaseAssetSource

A source that reads assets from the class-path. If this application is bundled in a jar then all resources bundled in the jar with it are accessible through this source.

Author:
Philip Diffenderfer

ClasspathSource

public ClasspathSource(String base)
Instantiates a new ClasspathSource with the given base and the default class loader.

Parameters:
base - The base to use to load assets. This base is effectively prepended to each request string. If null it will be handled as the default base.

ClasspathSource

public ClasspathSource(ClassLoader loader)
Instantiates a new ClasspathSource with the default base and the given class loader.

Parameters:
loader - The loader to use to load assets. The getResourceAsStream method is invoked on this loader when a request for an asset is made. If null it will be handled as the default class loader.

getLoader

public ClassLoader getLoader()

Returns:

getStream

public InputStream getStream(String request)
Description copied from interface: AssetSource
Returns an InputStream to the requested asset. If the asset doesn't exist in this source then an exception will be thrown or null will be returned depending on the implementation.

Parameters:
request - The request for the asset.
Returns:
The reference to InputStream containing the requested asset, or null if the request was invalid.
